    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_"><anchor id="AssymetricalMotion" styleclass="Heading3_atocs_"><keywords><keyword translate="true">Assymetric Motion</keyword></keywords></anchor><text styleclass="Heading3_atocs_" translate="true">Dwell-Rise-Dwell Asymmetric Motion</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="AStandard" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Symmetric Segments</text><text styleclass="Body Table" translate="true"> - </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">The </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Cross-Over" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">crossover</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true"> is</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> at the mid-point of the </text><text styleclass="Body Table" translate="true">Segment</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Asymmetric Motions</text><text styleclass="Body Table" translate="true"> - </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">The crossover is earlier or later than the mid-point of the </text><text styleclass="Body Table" translate="true">Segment</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true"> Use Asymmetric Motions</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> to modify the acceleration and deceleration timing. For example, if you want a tool to accelerate quickly, to reach its maximum velocity earlier than the mid-point of the segment, and then decelerate more gradually, or </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" translate="true">vice versa</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">You can model an asymmetrical motion with two segments that have the same motion-law. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:205px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MT-AsymmetricalModSine.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">This example Motion-Law is a </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Modified Sinusoid</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">. You would </text><text styleclass="VariableName-IT" translate="true">usually</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> specify this with one </text><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Mod-Sine</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> segment, but we will can imagine it as two segments.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_"><text styleclass="Interface2" style="color:#f79646;" translate="true">Orange Line graph</text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true"> - is Symmetrical</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Symmetrical Mod-Sine Motion-Law : λ = 0.5 </text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Segment</text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true"> 1</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Machine angle - X-axis: &#160;0 - 180º &#160;( 0 - 0.5 of total duration)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Displacement - Y-axis : 0 - 50 units </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Segment Ranges = Start-Range = 0 </text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">and </text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">End Range = 0.5</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Segment</text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true"> 2</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Machine angle - X-axis: &#160;180 - 360º ( 0.5 - 1.0 of total duration)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-style:normal;" translate="true">Displacement - Y-axis: &#160;50- 100 units</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Segment Ranges = Start-Range = 0.5</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">End-Range = 1</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Interface2"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Black Line graph </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">- is Asymmetrical</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Asymmetrical Mod-Sine Motion-Law : λ = 0.25</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Crossover @ 0.25 = 90º machine angle</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Interface2"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Segment 1: </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Machine angle - X-axis: 0 - 90º (0 - 0.25 of total duration)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Displacement - Y-axis: 0 - 25 units</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Segment Ranges = Start-Range = 0 </text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">and </text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">End Range = 0.5</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Interface2"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Segment 2: </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Machine angle - X-axis: 90 - 360º (0.25 - 1.0 of total duration)</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Displacement -Y-axis: 75 - 100 units</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Segment Ranges = Start-Range = 0.5</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">End-Range = 1</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Characteristics Values of Asymmetrical Motion-Law.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Maximum Velocity</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> : Asymmetrical Velocity = Symmetrical Velocity.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Maximum Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">: </text><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Segment 1</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> : &#160;C</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-size:7pt; vertical-align:sub;" translate="true">as</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> = C</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-size:7pt; vertical-align:sub;" translate="true">a </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">/ 2λ ; </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">Maximum Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">: </text><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">Segment 2</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> : &#160;C</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-size:7pt; vertical-align:sub;" translate="true">as</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> = C</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-size:7pt; vertical-align:sub;" translate="true">a </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">/ 2(1-λ)</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
